Note.Content: MT HOTTP-B NJPS ESV מִמֵּי יְהוּדָה "from the waters of Judah", by which "waters" symbolize semen | RSV NRSV "from the loins of Judah" =ממעי יהודה | REB "from the seed of Judah" = מזרע יהודה

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = action by which humans, animals, or objects leave a certain place or position
= causative action by which humans or deities cause (other) humans, animals, or objects to leave a certain place or position
literally: (one's) heart goes out; hence: = process by which humans lose courage and become afraid
literally: (one's) self goes out; hence: = process by which humans lose courage and become afraid
literally: to bring out (one's) spirit; hence: = action by which humans give full vent to their anger without holding anything back, ≈ which is regarded as a foolish deed
literally: to come out (of a group); hence: = process by which humans are a member of a certain community

Glosses.Gloss: to be one of a group

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to go out from; hence: = state in which part of an object is connected to the object itself in such as way that it seems as if it has grown out of it
= process of conception, described as going out from one's father's seed
literally: to go out (from the womb); hence: = process by which children are born
literally: to bring out (from the womb); hence: = causative process by which deities cause children to be born
literally: (God's) hand goes out (against someone); hence: = action by which a deities chastise humans ◄ as if by striking them physically with their hands
= process by which a construction project comes to an end
literally: (someone's) self goes out; hence: = process by which humans breathe their last and die
literally: (a year) goes out; hence: = process by which by which a period of time comes to an end
literally: to go out (to do something); hence: = action by which humans engage in a certain activity
literally: to go out as army; = state in which men qualify for military service
literally: to go out (from a circumstance); hence: = process by which humans are no longer affected by a certain circumstance
literally: to bring out (of a circumstance); hence: = causative process by which deities cause humans to be no longer affected by a certain circumstance
= process by which a substance such as food or semen leaves the body through one of its orifices
literally: to go out from; hence: = process by which a certain procedure results in a new product
literally: to bring out from; hence: = causative process by which humans carry out a certain procedure which results in a new product
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which an object vanishes from existence
literally: to come out (of a certain place); hence: = process by which liquids flow from a certain place
literally: to bring out (of a certain place); hence: = causative process by which humans or deities cause liquids to flow from a certain place
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which a person or object is no longer under someone else's control
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which an event starts taking place, originating from a certain deity, person, or place
literally: to bring out; hence: = causative process by which humans or deities cause an event to start taking place
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which an event stops taking place
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which certain information is becoming publicly known
literally: to bring out; hence: = causative process by which certain information is made publicly known
literally: to bring out a bad report; hence: = causative process by which humans publish bad information about something

Glosses.Gloss: to bring out a bad report

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to bring out a bad name; hence: = causative process by which humans say certain things about other humans that give them a bad reputation
literally: the lot comes out; hence: = process by which the lot has been thrown and the outcome has become clear
literally: to go out; hence: = process by which money is spent on a certain commodity
literally: to go out (from a location); hence: = process by which a certain commodity is purchased in a foreign location to be used locally
literally: to bring out (from a location); hence: = causative process by which humans sell a certain commodity to be used in a foreign location
literally: (someone's property) goes out; hence: = process by which humans lose possession of something
literally: to bring to light; hence: = causative process by which deities cause something that was previously hidden to become fully visible
literally: to come out; hence: = state in which an object extends into a certain direction
literally: (a boundary or measuring line) goes out; hence: = state in which a boundary or measuring line follows a certain trajectory
literally: (word) come out of (someone); hence: = process by which words are spoken by humans or deities
literally: to bring out; hence: = action by which humans utter words
literally: to come out; = process by which land or a living organism produces crops, branches, horns, or fruits
literally: to bring out; = causative process by which deities cause land, or objects to produce flowers or crops
read מצא
